                  <name xml:id="tag65" type="person">
          Philalethes
        </name>
               </rs>
            </add> It appears to me that<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="29"
                xml:id="pb-29"
                facs="#i29"/>
            <lb/>
25<lb/>
you attribute to science what in<lb/>
many cases has been the result of<lb/>
accident. The processes of most of<lb/>
the useful arts which you call<lb/>
chemical have been invented &amp; improved<lb/>
without any refined means, - without<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">any</del> general system of knowledge<lb/>
