                type="miscellaneous">
               <term xml:id="tag68">
          apollo
        </term>
            </rs> Belvedere be supposed to<lb/>
be owing to accidental combinations.<lb/>
In the progress of an art from its<lb/>
crudest to its more perfect state, the<lb/>
whole process depends upon experiments<lb/>
Science is in fact nothing more than<lb/>
the refinement of common sense, making<lb/>
use of facts already known to acquire<lb/>
new facts. Clays which are yellow are<lb/>
known to turn red; calcareous earth<lb/>
renders <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag69"
                ref="#chemical_106"
                type="chemical">
               <term xml:id="tag69">
          Flint
          
        </term>
            </rs> fusible. The persons who<lb/>
have improved <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">the pottery</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">earthen ware</add> made their<lb/>
selections accordingly. Iron was discovered<lb/>
at least 1000 grams before it was rendered<lb/>
malleable; &amp; from what <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
