            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">is produced</add> &amp; at length <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">a</add>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">soiled</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">soil</add> is formed in which<lb/>
grass can fix its roots. <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">i</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">I</add>n the crevices<lb/>
of walls where this soil is washed down<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="233"
                xml:id="pb-233"
                facs="#i233"/>
            <lb/>
229<lb/>
even the seeds of trees <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">can</del> grow,<lb/>
&amp; gradually as a building becomes more<lb/>
